# Shipped-template discipline

Follow the conventions documented in `docs/standards/templates.md`.

Key points:
- Every new or changed guard hook ships with a `test-<name>.sh` beside it
- Hooks fail open (exit 0 on missing deps/unknown payloads); denial is exit 2 via `hook_deny`
- Customization points live in marked TAILOR blocks or `harness.conf` — never in mechanism lines
- Provider-matrix facts carry a `verified YYYY-MM` stamp naming a primary source
- Mechanism behavior changes bump `plugins/harness-kit/.claude-plugin/plugin.json` before release
